- copy or clone lsmonitor to /etc/init.d/
- make the file executeable (chmod 755 /etc/init.d/lsmonitor)
- if you want to run on startup as service type: update-rc.d lsmonitor defaults
- install evtest and smartmontools type: apt-get install evtest smartmontools

- get up to date file from github: # git clone https://github.com/wenzhuoz/lsmonitor.git
